revision.text:
'''Artists Against Fracking''' is an association of artists initiated by [[Yoko Ono]] and her son, [[Sean Lennon]], also including [[Mark Ruffalo]], [[Robert de Niro]], [[Lady Gaga]], [[Paul McCartney]], and [[Deepak Chopra]]. 

==History==
As of August 2012, 180 artists were part of the group, which opposes natural gas drilling in the [[Marcellus shale]].<ref name="nyt">{{cite web | url=http://green.blogs.nytimes.com/2012/08/29/yoko-ono-and-sean-lennon-organize-artists-against-fracking/?_r=1 | title=Yoko Ono and Sean Lennon Organize Artists Against Fracking | publisher=New York Times | date=29 August 2012 | accessdate=17 May 2016 | author=Mireya Navarro}}</ref> 

In March 2013, the Independent Oil & Gas Association of New York filed a complaint with the [[New York Lobbying Board]] claiming the group had violated lobbying regulations,<ref name="fox">{{cite web | url=http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2013/03/30/ny-lobby-board-asked-to-investigate-yoko-ono-other-artists-against-fracking/ | title=NY lobby board asked to investigate Yoko Ono, other Artists Against Fracking | work=Fox News | date=March 30, 2013 | accessdate=18 May 2016 | author=Associated Press}}</ref> following an [[Associated Press]] news story suggesting that they should formally register as a lobbying group and had not done so.<ref>[http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/03/18/artists-against-fracking-lobbying_n_2899917.html artists-against-fracking-lobbying] 2013/03/18 TheHuffingtonPost.com, Inc. {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150216151651/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/03/18/artists-against-fracking-lobbying_n_2899917.html |date=February 16, 2015 }} </ref> As of late 2014, [[hydraulic fracking]] is prohibited in New York state.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.srf.ch/news/international/new-york-erlaesst-fracking-verbot|title=New York erlässt Fracking-Verbot|date=18 December 2014|location=Schweizer Radio und Fernsehen (in German)|access-date=16 December 2016}}</ref>

